        <font size='4'><b>FLYING HOUSE SEEN OVER MILLSBERRY</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20091105.JPG' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, November  5, 2009</b> &mdash;
    The other day, residents in Millsberry&#039;s Westridge neighborhood reported seeing <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/campaigns/up2009/">a house attached to balloons</a> and flying in the sky over Millsberry. A short while later residents in the Metro Park reported seeing a house land near the skating rink in the Park.<br><br>One citizen interviewed, who was in the park at the time with her dog, said, &quot;I was not at all surprised to see a house floating with balloons because I recently heard about a 78 year-old balloon salesman, I think <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/campaigns/up2009/">Carl</a> was his name, who tied thousands of balloons to his house and just flew away. Apparently, he wanted to go on a great adventure.&quot; We found that most Citizenry was incredibly surprised to see a flying house and that those in the park at the time surrounded the house immediately!<br>
<br>
After speaking to a number of eyewitnesses it turns out that the women with the dog was right as <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/campaigns/up2009/">Carl</a> emerged from the house almost as soon as it landed. However, he was not alone as others emerged including <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/campaigns/up2009/">Russell</a>, an overly optimistic 8 year old Wilderness Explorer; Dug, a lovable golden mutt with a remarkable high-tech collar that translates his thoughts into speech; and Kevin, an extremely rare 13&mdash;foot tall flightless bird.<br><br>It turns out that Carl, Russell, Kevin and Dug were just returning from a great adventure in South America and were passing over Millsberry when they hit turbulence causing a bunch of their <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/campaigns/up2009/">stuff to fall out of the house</a>. Now they are asking all Millsberry Citizens to help them collect it all so that they can continue on their way home! <br><br>The items dropped include costumes, <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=4">Dug&#039;s high-tech collar,</a> <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=3">Kevin&#039;s Head Feathers</a> and other items for your home. Carl, Russell, Dug and Kevin really appreciate your help and will be giving away random items to all  Millsberry Citizens who collect all 6 items that are scattered throughout Millsberry!<br><br>Lastly, they are giving away 2 items to everyone that visit their Millsberry page. <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/campaigns/up2009/">What are you waiting for? Go now!</a>
    </div>

